{
  "text": "Besides enhanced classification methods, postclassification operation is regarded as an effective way to improve the accuracy of a preclassified land cover map [CITATION_1] . For example, Mesev [CITATION_2] used population information in urban image postclassification sorting. To remove \"speckled\" or \"salt and pepper\" noise produced by pixel spectra-based classifiers, some noise removal methods were proposed [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In [CITATION_6] , postclassification correction was applied to improve land cover preclassification by incorporating ancillary data and knowledge-based logic rules. Textural analysis (using cooccurrence matrix) was used to conduct more accurate urban mapping from high spatial resolution satellite images [CITATION_7] , [CITATION_8] . Stefanov et al. [CITATION_9] and Kahya et al. [CITATION_10] adopted an expert system to sort initial land cover classification results using ancillary data (such as land use data).",
